place.name: BISCATHORPE
place.gazetteerText: BISCATHORPE, or Beskerthorpe, a parish in Louth district, Lincoln; on the river Bane, 8 miles WSW of Louth r. station. Post Town, Donington, under Louth. Acres, 1,050. Real property, £1,3 70. Pop., 90. Houses, 11. The property is divided among a few. The living is annexed to Gayton-le-Wold. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
